question: Oliver places cookies on some baskets. Each basket can hold 35 cookies. If he has 140 cookies and 2 baskets, how many cookies won't he be able to place on the basket?
answer:
Oliver will be able to place a total of 35*2 = <<35*2=70>>70 cookies.
Therefore, there are 140 - 70 = <<140-70=70>>70 cookies that he won't be able to place on the basket.
#### 70
